<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911017-0034</DOCNO><DOCID>911017-0034.</DOCID><HL>   Hadson Agrees to Sell   Power Systems Unit   To LGandamp;E Energy</HL><DATE>10/17/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8</SO><CO>   HAD LGE</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)OIL-SECONDARY (OIS)PETROLEUM (PET)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>PETROLEUM MARKET (PET)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>KENTUCKY (KY)NORTH AMERICA (NME)OKLAHOMA (OK)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   OKLAHOMA CITY -- Hadson Corp. said it signed a letter ofintent to sell its Hadson Power Systems unit to LGandamp;E EnergyCorp. for $53 million.   The agreement calls for Hadson to retain ownership of sixCalifornia cogeneration projects and a waste-wood processingfacility. Hadson also will retain economic interests in someengineering and construction projects.</LP><TEXT>   Hadson said the sale requires the approval of thecompanies' boards and regulatory authorities; the companyexpects the sale to be completed in early December. Hadsonsaid the purchase price may increase by $3.5 million undercertain circumstances related to one of the cogenerationprojects.   Announcement of the proposed sale to LGandamp;E, the Louisville,Ky., parent of Louisville Gas andamp; Electric Co., comes only daysafter Hadson terminated its contract to sell the powersystems unit to an affiliate of BrightStar Group Ltd. andPiazza andamp; Co. for $65 million. The BrightStar/Piazza purchasehad been delayed because of financing difficulties, andHadson said that the purchase agreement allowed either partyto terminate it if the transaction didn't close by a certaindate.   Hadson is an independent producer and supplier of energyproducts and services.</TEXT></DOC>